subsections.bareActText:
(62) "input tax" in relation to a taxable person, means the central tax, State tax, integrated tax or Union territory tax charged on any supply of goods or services or both made to him and includes—
(a) the integrated goods and services tax charged on import of goods;
(b) the tax payable under the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 9, but does not include the tax paid under the composition levy;
